track_notes: Just under a mile off-trail hike with 740 EG.  Parking for a couple of cars at a small pull-off on Hwy 178 (35.012394, -82.795481).  Head north a few yards and cross the highway into the first ravine.  Follow the flagging heading up the north side of the ravine to gain the ridgeline.  Follow the ridgeline to the summit. This route does skirt a private parcel, but I never saw any boundary markers.  Typical hardwood summit.

2.4 mile hike with 900 EG on gated forest and logging roads, descending off-trail from the summit back to the forest road.  Parking for several cars at small pull off on the eastern side of Hwy 178 (35.0105, -82.7998).  Starting on the gated road across from the parking area, hike 0.4 miles to a T-intersection and head to the right.  Follow this road for about 0.2 miles to a three way fork.  Take the logging road to the left and climb steeply to the ridgeline and the summit is a short distance to the left.  From the summit, I headed off-trail south from the summit through open forest with nice rock outrcops and joing the original route near the first T-intersection.
track_title: W4C/US-015 - Rich Mtn Loop from Hwy 178

track_notes: Parking for 2-3 cars at trailhead for the Upper Twin Falls (35.00494, -82.81366).  From this trailhead, you can take one of two routes or can do a bit of a loop hike.  Both routes are ~1.6 miles long with 1300 EG, the ridge trail climbs steeply for the first 0.6 miles then levels off where the valley trail climbs steadily till the two meet back up.  A couple hundred feet from the road the Reedy River Cove Falls trail turns to the left and you will take the logging road to the right.  At the first intersection take the logging road to the left uphill.  Very soon you will come to another intersection of logging roads where you will have to make your decision, left again to climb the ridge trail or stay straight/right to take the valley trail.  At the gap (or before) turn to the right and follow the ridge line to the summit.
track_title: From Cleo Chapman Highway - Ridge Trail
